{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01671L1ZX2q6qnuw5NkwpQ7u","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Summary**\n\nThe root cause of snapshot failures was a missing MinIO service (DNS resolution failed) and the `repository-s3` plugin not being installed.\n\n**Steps taken:**\n\n1. **Created MinIO Service** (`minio` in the `elasticsearch` namespace) — the `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` DNS name was unresolvable because no service existed.\n\n2. **Created `es-secure-settings` Secret** — stored MinIO credentials (`s3.client.default.access_key` / `s3.client.default.secret_key`) in a Kubernetes Secret, not in `elasticsearch.yml` or environment variables.\n\n3. **Created `es-backups` bucket** in MinIO via a Job (the original `minio-init` job failed because the service didn't exist).\n\n4. **Updated `elasticsearch.yml` ConfigMap** with non-sensitive S3 client settings: endpoint URL, HTTP protocol, and path-style access (required for MinIO).\n\n5. **Patched the StatefulSet** with two init containers:\n   - `install-s3-plugin`: downloads and installs the `repository-s3` plugin into a shared emptyDir, which the main container sees mounted at `plugins/repository-s3/`\n   - `setup-keystore`: creates a fresh keystore, reads credentials from the `es-secure-settings` Secret via env vars, and also pre-populates `bootstrap.password` (to prevent the ES entrypoint from trying to write to the read-only bind-mounted keystore file)\n\n6. **Registered `minio-repo`** snapshot repository (type: s3, bucket: es-backups).\n\n7. **Created `snapshot-1`** — completed in 4.2 seconds with all 4 shards successful, state: `SUCCESS`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":460,"cache_read_input_tokens":79649,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":460},"out